[normal](13) This represents a drastic break with UNRWA’s early practice. In 1950, its first d
[normal]irector told the 
[normal]General Assembly that the “a
[normal]gency has decided that a refugee is a needy person, who, as a result of the war in Palestine, has lost his home 
[normal]and his means of livelihood.
[normal]”
[normal] His definition made no reference to descendants.
[normal](14) 
[normal]Not until 
[normal]1965, fifteen years after its 
[normal]creation, did a
[normal]n UNRWA commissioner g
[normal]eneral decide, against objections from the 
[normal]Unite
[normal]d States
[normal] government, to create “
[normal]an extension o
[normal]f eligibility, subject to need, to the third generation of refugees (that is, to children of persons who were themselves born after 14 May 1948).
[normal]”
[normal] 
[normal]And even then, he extended eligibility only to the third generation, the grandchildren.
[normal] According to Benjami
[normal]n Schiff, Commissioner General Laurence 
[normal]Michelmore
[normal]’s motive was driven by a short term budget imperative to “
[normal]enlist the host-states
[normal]’
[normal] assistance in cut
[normal]&#xad;
[normal]ting the rolls
[normal] ...
[normal] he had offered a trade: If the governments would help rectify the rolls, he would be w
[normal]illing to
[normal] ... 
[normal]add third-generation refugees to the rolls.
[normal]”
[normal](15) I
[normal]n 1982, 
[normal]thirty-two years after its creation, UNRWA 
[normal]took another step
[normal] forward by 
[normal]extend
[normal]ing 
[normal]eligibility to
[normal] all 
[normal]generations of descendants. 
[normal]It did so by obtaining a General Assembly Resolution
[normal] 
[normal]instructing UNRWA “
[normal]to issue identification cards to all Palestine 
[normal]refugees and their descendants”
[normal] 
[normal]without any limitation on how many generations of descendancy
[normal] this practice would continue. 
[normal]This momentous decision was adopted without a 
[normal]specific debate or 
[normal]separate 
[normal]vote in the General Assembly.
[normal](16) 
[normal]U
[normal]NRWA went still further in 1992
[normal] by adding a provision that those
[normal] d
[normal]escendants
[normal] 
[normal]of Palestine refugee males who “
[normal]are eligible
[normal] to register for UNRWA services”
[normal] and are registered with UNRWA, should be 
[normal]“referred to as Registered Refugees or as Registered Palestine Refugees” 
[normal][AU: emphasis added
[normal]?
[normal] ??
[normal]] though they do not meet UNRWA’
